view.name: Conceptual Solution Architecture
view.documentation:
Conceptual Solution Architecture : Establishes the solution vision and contex.
* Business Process Graphic : Shows the abstract business context for the solution and how the solution supports the business context.
* Layer Graphic : Shows the delineation of business functionality and technology elements.
* User Interaction Graphic : Shows the users and their interactions with the solution.
* Solution Concept Graphic : Shows organizations, stakeholders, users, systems, and technologies, within the solution and their respective interactions.

view.name: Logical Solution Architecture
view.documentation:
Confirms the Solution design that will be implemented.
* System Function Graphic: Shows the allocation of application, data, messaging functions in the conceptual layer graphic to elements within the building block graphic.
* Information / Control Flow Graphic : Graphic that details how information is flowing and controlled among the logical solution elements.
* Integrated Design Graphic : A logical level solution overview showing some physical details covering all solution elements in order to understand key technical issues .
